<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-688-408  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 688 408.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  Sept 25 1989 n334 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Gallup poll looks at software. (software market and sales trends)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Caginalp, Elizabeth G.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Gallup Organization Inc surveyed software buying trends amongthe country's fastest-emerging companies, revealing that 84percent of them buy software packages from the channel.andO;Approximately 22 percent of the companies buy from manufacturersand about 18 percent buy via direct-mail.andP;  Eighty-nine percent ofthe companies polled from the ranks of Inc. magazine's list of thefastest-growing US private and small public companies, operatewith the MS-DOS/PC-DOS operating environment.andP;  However, UNIX/Xenixand Macintosh environments show signs of growing.andP;  OS/2environment is used by only 11 percent, but by next year thatpercent will rise to 21 percent.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     SoftwareTrendsSurveyValue-Added ResellersSmall BusinessMS-DOSGallup Poll.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   Software facts on fast-growth firms. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>